D Professional Disc System |publisher=Sony |accessdate=23 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060504105940/http://bssc.sel.sony.com/BroadcastandBusiness/docs/brochures/v-2320.pdf |archivedate=4 May 2006 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| rowspan=2 | {{convert|3.85|kg|order=flip|disp=br|abbr=on}}{{efn|Approximately {{convert|5.4|kg|order=flip|abbr=on}} with viewfinder, microphone, Professional Disc, and battery}}\n| rowspan=2 | {{convert|124|\u00d7|268|\u00d7|328|mm|order=flip|disp=br|abbr=on}}\n| rowspan=2 | 3\u00d7{{frac|1|2}}\"<br/>CCD\n| rowspan=2 | Sony {{frac|1|2}}\" bayonet\n| rowspan=2 | [[XDCAM]] [[Professional Disc|PFD]]\n| 4\u201360 ([[1080p]])\n| rowspan=2 | 2006\n| rowspan=2 | [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]]&nbsp;No\n|-\n! PDW-F330<ref name=XDCAM-F350-F330 />\n| 24,25,30 ([[1080p]])<br/>50,60 ([[1080i]])\n|-\n! PMW-EX1/EX1R<ref name=XDCAM-EX>{{cite web |url=https://pro.sony/s3/cms-static-content/file/65/1237485216665.pdf |title=XDCAM EX |publisher=Sony |accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://pro.sony/s3/cms-static-content/file/44/1237485157844.pdf |title=Full HD solid-state camcorder. PMW-EX1R |publisher=Sony |accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref>\n| {{convert|2.4|kg|order=flip|disp=br|abbr=on}}{{efn|Approximately {{convert|2.8|kg|order=flip|abbr=on}} with battery and SxS card.}}\n| {{convert|178|\u00d7|176|\u00d7|311.5|mm|order=flip|disp=br|abbr=on}}{{efn|name=withLens|With lens.}}\n| rowspan=2 | 3\u00d7{{frac|1|2}}\"<br/>CMOS\n| Fixed\n| rowspan=2 | 2\u00d7[[SxS]]\n| rowspan=2 | 1\u201330 ([[1080p]])<br/>1\u201360 ([[720p]])\n| 2007<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.networkworld.com/article/2252403/smb/sony-announces-replacement-for-the-pmw-ex1.html |title=Sony announces replacement for the PMW-EX1 |author=Young, Rick |date=23 October 2009 |work=Network World |accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref>{{efn|EX1R announced in 2009 with upgraded features.}}\n| rowspan=2 | [[File:X mark.svg|15px|No]]&nbsp;No\n|-\n! PMW-EX3<ref 