{"title_page": "Bolton Group", "text_new": "{{db-spam|help=off}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Bolton Group\n| logo = \n| type = \n| industry = Consumer goods \n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = <!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], country -->\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = [[Milan]]\n| hq_location_country = [[Italy]]\n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = Marina Nissim (CEO)<ref name=\"Seafood 2019\" />\n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = >11,000<ref name=\"Our Numbers\" >{{cite web |title=OUR NUMBERS |url=http://www.boltongroup.net/en-ww/group/group |website=www.boltongroup.net |publisher=Bolton Group |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|www.boltongroup.net/en-ww/brands/brands}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Bolton Group''' is an Italian [[conglomerate]] which sells products under more than fifty brands. \n\n==Overview==\nThe Bolton Groups is a conglomerate which sells products under more than 50 brands. The majority of their business is food related. They are based in [[Milan]], [[Italy]].<ref name=\"Our Numbers\" />\n\n==History==\nThe Bolton Group was founded Joseph Nissim, a Greek immigrant to Italy. Joseph Nissim was born in 1919 and escaped [[Thessaloniki]] when the Nazis invaded Greece. After fleeing Greece he joined the [[British Army]] and fought with distinction at the [[battle of El Alamein]]. He settled in Italy in 1949. He died age 100 in 2019.<ref name=\"Joseph Nissim obit\" >{{cite web |title=Bolton founder Joseph Nissim dies aged 100 |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2019/03/18/bolton-founder-joseph-nissim-dies-aged-100/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 the Bolton Group had \u20ac1.96 billion in revenue and  \u20ac210.8 million in profits.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pekic |first1=Branislav |title=Bolton Group Sees 11.6% Revenue Growth In 2016 |url=https://www.esmmagazine.com/index.php/a-brands/bolton-group-sees-revenue-growth-2016-48573 |website=www.esmmagazine.com |publisher=European Supermarket Magazine |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs a result of the [[COVID-19]] epidemic sales of the Bolton Group\u2019s canned seafood products boomed in Europe.<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" >{{cite web |last1=Mereghetti |first1=Matilde |title=Bolton sees canned tuna sales boom in EU lockdowns |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2020/03/31/bolton-sees-canned-tuna-sales-boom-in-eu-lockdowns/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThey are a leading [[Consolidation (business)|consolidator]] in the tuna and seafood industries.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seaman |first1=Tom |title=Bolton vs Thai Union: Different approaches to tuna consolidation |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2015/06/22/bolton-vs-thai-union-different-approaches-to-tuna-consolidation/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries== \n===Tri Marine===\nTri Marine is one of the three largest global [[tuna]] traders along with [[FCF Co, Ltd.|FCF]] and [[Itochu]].<ref name=\"Choppy Waters\" >{{cite web |title=Choppy Waters, Forced Labour and Illegal Fishing in Taiwan\u2019s Distant Water Fisheries |url=https://www.greenpeace.org/usa/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/b87c6229-2020-choppy-waters-en.pdf |website=www.greenpeace.org |publisher=Greenpeace |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> Tri Marine is based in [[Bellevue, Washington]] and was founded in 1971. In 2019 Tri Marine was sold to the Bolton Group.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seaman |first1=Tom |title=Bolton inks deal to take control of Tri Marine\u2019s tuna supply business |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2019/07/06/bolton-inks-deal-to-take-control-of-tri-marines-tuna-supply-business/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> Tri Marine has more than 5,000 employees and operates 16 [[purse seine|purse-seiners]].<ref name=\"Seafood 2019\" >{{cite web |last1=White |first1=Cliff |title=Tri Marine sold to Bolton Group |url=https://www.seafoodsource.com/news/business-finance/tri-marine-sold-to-bolton-group |website=www.seafoodsource.com |publisher=Seafood Source |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> After the sale Tri Marine named Juan Corrales as the new CEO replacing Renato Curto who had held the position for 35 years.<ref name=\"Intrafish 2019\" >{{cite web |last1=Fiorillo |first1=John |title=Tuna giant Tri Marine names new CEO |url=https://www.intrafish.com/fisheries/tuna-giant-tri-marine-names-new-ceo/2-1-721743 |website=www.intrafish.com |publisher=Intrafish |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Rio Mare=== \nRio Mare is an Italian seafood company which is now a Bolton Group brand/subsidiary.<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" /> In 2017 Rio Mare launched a brand of organic tuna certified by the [[Marine Stewardship Council]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pekic |first1=Branislav |title=Seafood Brand Rio Mare Launches Organic Tuna Range In Italy |url=https://www.esmmagazine.com/index.php/a-brands/rio-mare-launches-organic-canned-tuna-italy-42862 |website=www.esmmagazine.com |publisher=European Supermarket Magazine |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref> Rio Mare operates a factory in [[Cermenate]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Arosio |first1=Alessandra |title=Italy's Rio Mare Decreased Water Consumption By 7% In 2018 |url=https://www.esmmagazine.com/index.php/a-brands/italys-rio-mare-decreased-water-consumption-7-2018-72660 |website=www.esmmagazine.com |publisher=European Supermarket Magazine |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Brands==\n* Palmera - Italian canned seafood<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" />\n* Saupiquet - French canned seafood<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" />\n* Isabel - Spanish canned seafood<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" />\n* Garavilla - Spanish seafood<ref name=\"Intrafish 2019\" />\n* Petreet - Pet food<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" />\n* Ocean Naturals - Seafood<ref name=\"Seafood 2019\" />\n* Choice landing - Seafood<ref name=\"Seafood 2019\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Milan]]\n[[Category:Fishing industry]]\n", "text_old": "{{db-spam|help=off}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Bolton Group\n| logo = \n| type = \n| industry = Consumer goods \n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = <!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], country -->\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = [[Milan]]\n| hq_location_country = [[Italy]]\n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = Marina Nissim (CEO)<ref name=\"Seafood 2019\" />\n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = >11,000<ref name=\"Our Numbers\" >{{cite web |title=OUR NUMBERS |url=http://www.boltongroup.net/en-ww/group/group |website=www.boltongroup.net |publisher=Bolton Group |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n| num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) -->\n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|www.boltongroup.net/en-ww/brands/brands}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Bolton Group''' is an Italian [[conglomerate]] which sells products under more than fifty brands. \n\n==Overview==\nThe Bolton Groups is a conglomerate which sells products under more than 50 brands. The majority of their business is food related. They are based in [[Milan]], [[Italy]].<ref name=\"Our Numbers\" />\n\n==History==\nThe Bolton Group was founded Joseph Nissim a Greek immigrant to Italy. Joseph Nissim was born in 1919 and escaped [[Thessaloniki]] when the Nazis invaded Greece. After fleeing Greece he joined the [[British Army]] and fought with distinction at the [[battle of El Alamein]]. He settled in Italy in 1949. He died age 100 in 2019.<ref name=\"Joseph Nissim obit\" >{{cite web |title=Bolton founder Joseph Nissim dies aged 100 |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2019/03/18/bolton-founder-joseph-nissim-dies-aged-100/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 the Bolton Group had \u20ac1.96 billion in revenue and  \u20ac210.8 million in profits.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pekic |first1=Branislav |title=Bolton Group Sees 11.6% Revenue Growth In 2016 |url=https://www.esmmagazine.com/index.php/a-brands/bolton-group-sees-revenue-growth-2016-48573 |website=www.esmmagazine.com |publisher=European Supermarket Magazine |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs a result of the [[COVID-19]] epidemic sales of the Bolton Group\u2019s canned seafood products boomed in Europe.<ref name=\"Undercurrent 2020\" >{{cite web |last1=Mereghetti |first1=Matilde |title=Bolton sees canned tuna sales boom in EU lockdowns |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2020/03/31/bolton-sees-canned-tuna-sales-boom-in-eu-lockdowns/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThey are a leading [[Consolidation (business)|consolidator]] in the tuna and seafood industries.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seaman |first1=Tom |title=Bolton vs Thai Union: Different approaches to tuna consolidation |url=https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2015/06/22/bolton-vs-thai-union-different-approaches-to-tuna-consolidation/ |website=www.undercurrentnews.com |publisher=Undercurrent News |accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries== \n===Tri Marine===\nTri Marine is one of the three largest global [[tuna]] traders along with [[FCF Co, Ltd.|FCF]] and [[Itochu]].<ref name=\"Choppy Waters\" >{{cite web |title=Choppy Waters, Forced Labour and Illegal Fishing in Taiwan\u2019s Distant Water Fisheries |url=https://www.greenpeace.org/usa/wp